        DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN 

             CCTTIIMMEE converts a long integer, pointed to by _c_l_o_c_k, 
             representing the time in seconds since 00:00:00, January 1, 
             1970, and returns a pointer to a 26-character string in the 
             following form: 

                  Sun Sep 16 01:03:52 1973\n\0 

             The TTIIMMEE function is ideally suited to return the long 
             interger time value.  

             LLOOCCAALLTTIIMMEE returns a pointer to the _t_m structure.  

             AASSCCTTIIMMEE converts a _t_m structure to a 26-character string, 
             as shown in the above example, and returns a pointer to the 
             string.  

             For user convience, declarations of all the functions and 
             the externals, and the _t_m structure, are provided in the 
             <utime.h> header file, shown on the next page.  

             The external long variable _t_i_m_e_z_o_n_e is always zero.  

        EEXXAAMMPPLLEE 

